Wang","line":102},{"title":"Author/Peipei Wang","target":"Author/Peipei Wang","line":103},{"title":"Author/Cun Zhao","target":"Author/Cun Zhao","line":104},{"title":"Author/Cun Zhao","target":"Author/Cun Zhao","line":105},{"title":"Author/Jian Yao","target":"Author/Jian Yao","line":106},{"title":"Author/Jian Yao","target":"Author/Jian Yao","line":107},{"title":"Author/Peng Xia","target":"Author/Peng Xia","line":108},{"title":"Author/Peng Xia","target":"Author/Peng Xia","line":109},{"title":"Author/Peng Xia","target":"Author/Peng Xia","line":110},{"title":"Author/Gang Pei","target":"Author/Gang Pei","line":111},{"title":"Author/Gang Pei","target":"Author/Gang Pei","line":112},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/huang_polysaccharides_2017/huang_polysaccharides_2017.pdf","line":114}],"metadata":{"id":"huang_polysaccharides_2017","type":"article-journal","title":"Polysaccharides from Ganoderma lucidum Promote Cognitive Function and Neural Progenitor Proliferation in Mouse Model of Alzheimer's Disease","issued":{"date-parts":[[2017]]},"DOI":"10.1016/j.stemcr.2016.12.007","container-title":"Stem cell reports","abstract":"Promoting neurogenesis is a promising strategy for the treatment of cognition impairment associated with Alzheimer's disease (AD). Ganoderma lucidum is a revered medicinal mushroom for health-promoting benefits in the Orient. Here, we found that oral administration of the polysaccharides and water extract from G.lucidum promoted neural progenitor cell (NPC) proliferation to enhance neurogenesis and alleviated cognitive deficits in transgenic AD mice. G.lucidum polysaccharides (GLP) also promoted self-renewal of NPC in cell culture. Further mechanistic study revealed that GLP potentiated activation of fibroblast growth factor receptor 1 (FGFR1) and downstream extracellular signal-regulated kinase (ERK) and AKT cascades. Consistently, inhibition of FGFR1 effectively blocked the GLP-promoted NPC proliferation and activation of the downstream cascades. Our findings suggest that GLP could serve as a regenerative therapeutic agent for the treatment of cognitive decline associated with neurodegenerative diseases.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Huang","given":"Shichao","literal":""},{"family":"Huang","given":"Shichao","literal":""},{"family":"Mao","given":"Jianxin","literal":""},{"family":"Mao","given":"Jianxin","literal":""},{"family":"Ding","given":"Kan","literal":""},{"family":"Ding","given":"Kan","literal":""},{"family":"Zhou","given":"Yue","literal":""},{"family":"Zhou","given":"Yue","literal":""},{"family":"Zeng","given":"Xiangfeng","literal":""},{"family":"Zeng","given":"Xianglu","literal":""},{"family":"Yang","given":"Wuyi","literal":""},{"family":"Yang","given":"Wenjuan","literal":""},{"family":"Wang","given":"Peipei","literal":""},{"family":"Wang","given":"Peipei","literal":""},{"family":"Zhao","given":"Cun","literal":""},{"family":"Zhao","given":"Cun","literal":""},{"family":"Yao","given":"Jian","literal":""},{"family":"Yao","given":"Jian","literal":""},{"family":"Xia","given":"Peng","literal":""},{"family":"Xia","given":"Peng","literal":""},{"family":"Xia","given":"Peng","literal":""},{"family":"Pei","given":"Gang","literal":""},{"family":"Pei","given":"Gang","literal":""}],"citation-key":"huang_polysaccharides_2017","year":"2017","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Polysaccharides from Ganoderma lucidum Promote Cognitive Function and Neural Progenitor Proliferation in Mouse Model of Alzheimer's Disease"],"author-links":["[[Author/Shichao Huang]]","[[Author/Shichao Huang]]","[[Author/Jianxin Mao]]","[[Author/Jianxin Mao]]","[[Author/Kan Ding]]","[[Author/Kan Ding]]","[[Author/Yue Zhou]]","[[Author/Yue Zhou]]","[[Author/Xiangfeng Zeng]]","[[Author/Xianglu Zeng]]","[[Author/Wuyi Yang]]","[[Author/Wenjuan Yang]]","[[Author/Peipei Wang]]","[[Author/Peipei Wang]]","[[Author/Cun Zhao]]","[[Author/Cun Zhao]]","[[Author/Jian Yao]]","[[Author/Jian Yao]]","[[Author/Peng Xia]]",